Station: PEACE RIVER, AT FORT VERMILION - CENTRE
SampleComment: Sampled from electric ice auger hole, ~15 m out from the boat laumch area on right bank. Direct filled metals, bacti, and ultra-trace Hg and MeHg bottles by hand, below ice, as clamp for stainless steel rod was frozen. Samples arrived for processing in Edmonton either partially or entirely frozen. All were sent for analysisexcept the total Hg bottle, which had frozen and broken during transport. Total Hg was still analyzed, using water from the TMeHg bottle. See COC's with notes on condition, saved in DIVA.

Station: PEACE RIVER, AT FORT VERMILION - CENTRE
SampleComment: Filled bottles from carboy, using weighted sampler, through a hole chipped in the fresh ice cover, ~40 m out off right bank at boat launch area. Used weighted sampler to direct fill PAH bottles, used stainless steel rod and clamp to direct fill metals and bacti bottles, and filled Hg and MeHg bottles directly by hand, reaching under ice. Ice front passed through sample location approximately 48 hrs prior to sample collection.

Used carboy and weighted sampler to fill BV samples, isotopes, and chlorophyll, used weighted sampler to direct fill PAH bottles, and reached under ice with long gloves to direct fill bacti, metals, and Hg and MeHg samples.
